    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Saying 'Hello'",
          "arabic": "تحية 'أهلاً'"
        },
        "text": "The most common way to say \"hello\" in Egyptian Arabic is \"أهلاً\". You can also say \"أهلاً وسهلاً\" for a more formal and welcoming greeting, often used when welcoming someone to a place.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أهلاً",
            "english": "Hello",
            "transliteration": "Ahlan"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أهلاً وسهلاً",
            "english": "Hello / Welcome",
            "transliteration": "Ahlan wa sahlan"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "Ahlan. Ahlan wa sahlan."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How are you?'",
          "arabic": "سؤال 'إزيك؟'"
        },
        "text": "To ask \"How are you?\" in Egyptian Arabic, you say \"إزيك؟\". The pronunciation of the last letter changes slightly depending on whether you are speaking to a male or a female.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "إزيكَ؟",
            "english": "How are you? (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Izzayak?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "إزيكِ؟",
            "english": "How are you? (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "Izzayik?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "Izzayak? Izzayik?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Stating Your Name",
          "arabic": "ذكر اسمك"
        },
        "text": "To introduce your name, you say \"اسمي\" followed by your name. \"اسمي\" literally means \"my name is...\".",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "اسمي أحمد.",
            "english": "My name is Ahmed.",
            "transliteration": "Ismi Ahmed."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "اسمي سارة.",
            "english": "My name is Sara.",
            "transliteration": "Ismi Sara."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "Ismi Ahmed. Ismi Sara."
      }
    },
